<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[701,1227,1642,1754]" lastBlockId="18.[128,654,211,1754]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">DIAGNOSIS: Distinctive species with bold, contrasting blackish-brown and light yellow markings: ocellar triangle, scutum, scutellum, postnotum, anepisternum, tIV+V (males; in females also tVIII+IX) dark blackish brown, rest of body light yellowish. Wing entirely hyaline. Cerci with two pairs of large, stiff setae ventrally; distiphallus long, slender.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5358049" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5358049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5358049/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" startId="17.[112,150,1641,1663]" targetBox="[95,1180,210,1607]" targetPageId="17">
